——ЩRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2025-04-25-twin0296.mdЩ@83fc33e824b2eb3049726cd5fe2bd6984b23e6dd9ae203effb72c60a76aed793Щ"title: 'This week in Nushell #296'‘ЄHighlightsЪ



Ack! I'm late; I'm late! TWiN #296 apologies for this week's delay. Something about a dog, homework, and a giant bouncy house?
Wow - @Kissaki did some awesome work in 
``nu_scripts``
 with 
15 PRs
! Thank you!
Another new Polars command joins the team courtesy of @MMesch вЂ” 
``polars join_where``
.

Did you know that brings us to a total of 
three
 SQL-like 
``join``
 commands in Nushell?
Job control continues to progress with @cosineblast's addition of tags! And as a sneak preview, there's a special

job-control surprise in store that just missed the cutoff for this week's TWiN. You can read all about it in ...
The 0.104 release notes! That's right - This week is release week!
As always, special thanks to 
all
 our wonderful contributors for the PRs below.
’ђђЪITitle: title: 'This week in Nushell #296'
Path: Highlights
Content:




Ack! I'm late; I'm late! TWiN #296 apologies for this week's delay. Something about a dog, homework, and a giant bouncy house?
Wow - @Kissaki did some awesome work in 
``nu_scripts``
 with 
15 PRs
! Thank you!
Another new Polars command joins the team courtesy of @MMesch вЂ” 
``polars join_where``
.

Did you know that brings us to a total of 
three
 SQL-like 
``join``
 commands in Nushell?
Job control continues to progress with @cosineblast's addition of tags! And as a sneak preview, there's a special

job-control surprise in store that just missed the cutoff for this week's TWiN. You can read all about it in ...
The 0.104 release notes! That's right - This week is release week!
As always, special thanks to 
all
 our wonderful contributors for the PRs below.
—ЩRarchive/external_nushell_repo_backup/nushell.github.io/blog/2025-04-25-twin0296.mdЩ@3e31a40e20e07eab554cdbac3e2d5d60a5ab9e516143cbc68693454fe3cb2cc0Щ"title: 'This week in Nushell #296'‘§NushellЪ=Bahex 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15644] added 
``:nu``
 back to the help text in explore
.
cptpiepmatz 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15643] added 
``cat``
 and 
``get-content``
 to 
``open``
's search terms
.
pyz4 made several improvements and fixes for Polars:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15637] Fixed conversion from nanoseconds to time_units in Datetime and Duration parsing
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15632] Enabled parsing decimals in Polars schemas
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15608] Removed the requirement that pivot columns must be the same type in 
``polars pivot``
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15599] Mapped the 
``//``
 operator to FloorDivide for custom values and in Polars
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15598] Added the 
``pow``
 (
``**``
) operator for Polars expressions
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15590] Enabled 
``as_date``
 and 
``as_datetime``
 to handle expressions as inputs
.
MMesch:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15635] Added the 
``polars join_where``
 command
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15621] Fixed a mistake in the description of the Polars pivot command
.
sholderbach 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15634] fixed the labeling of plugins through the correct glob
.
SkillFlame 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15631] fixed an issue where 
``to md``
 breaks on tables with empty values
.
LoicRiegel:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15630] Fixed the output of 
``start_timestamp``
 as datetime instead of string in SQLite history tables
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15629] Made 
``str join``
 output dates consistently (RFC2822 when possible)
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15606] Fixed the loss of precision when parsing values with units
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15600] Added support for creating durations from records
.
AucaCoyan 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15627] added a labeler bot
.
sebasnallar 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15626] added the 
``--follow-symlinks``
 flag to the 
``glob``
 command
.
WindSoilder:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15623] Raised a reasonable error when using subexpressions with the 
``and``
 operator
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15617] Allowed subexpressions with redirection in IR
.
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15566] Kept PWD after activating an overlay through a file
.
suimong 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15614] improved the performance of 
``std/log``
.
hfrentzel 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15611] enabled running scripts of any file extension in PATHEXT on Windows
.
blindFS 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15603] fixed a regression in semantic tokens for module-prefixed commands
.
scarlet-storm 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15597] enabled SOCKS proxy support in ureq
.
fdncred 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15591] added more details to 
``describe -d``
.
Tyarel8 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15588] fixed 
``kv set``
 with a closure argument
.
NotTheDr01ds 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15569] added env-conversion helpers to 
``std``
.
cosineblast 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15555] added job tags
.
lazenga 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/15472] fixed outer joins incorrectly removing unmatched rows
.
